DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: DC link overvoltage
DiagMessage.Description: DC link overvoltage because the brake power of the power supply module is too low.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parameterization of the brake chopper from the power supply module is wrong.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameterization of the brake chopper from the power supply module.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong selection of the brake resistor from the power supply module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the resistance of the brake resistor. Check the power of the brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The brake resistor from the power supply module is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Measure the current resistance of the brake resistor.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Fan speed seems to be zero.
DiagMessage.Description: Fan speed seems to be zero.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The velocity signal of the cooling fan is zero.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the cooling fan.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Supply undervoltage: supply +24V
DiagMessage.Description: Supply undervoltage: supply +24V

CauseRemedy.Cause: The 24V Supply Voltage went under 18V.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply controlword, torque off order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a torque off order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply controlword, live counter inactive
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device controlword contains a live counter which didn't increment for the maximum accepted timespan.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply status is not alive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply status is linked to the Supply Device and the Device is in EtherCAT OP state.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply controlword, NC handling order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a NC handling order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply controlword, non-regenerative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a non-regenerative brake order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply controlword, regenerative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a regenerative brake order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Supply overvoltage: supply +24V
DiagMessage.Description: Supply overvoltage: supply +24V

CauseRemedy.Cause: The 24V Supply Voltage went over 40V.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your 24V supply voltage.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Parameter error in Object 0x%x/%x
DiagMessage.Description: The mentioned parameter contains a not accepted value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something is wrong with the parameters in this object.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the parameters of the mentioned object.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is above Maximum (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is above the maximum.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task is above the supported maximum value of this drive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a shorter Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is below Minimum (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is below the minimum.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task is below the supported minimum value of this drive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a longer Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is not a multiple of the Sync0 Cycle Time (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is not a multiple of the Sync0 Cycle Time.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task has to be a multiple of the drives Sync0 Cycle Time.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a valid Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync0 Cycle Time (%u ns) is unequal %u ns.
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is not the default Cycle Time.

Entry.Name: [SG] Controlword
Entry.Comment: This object shall indicate the received command controlling the PDS FSA. - Bit 0: Switch on - Bit 1: Enable voltage - Bit 2: Quick stop - Bit 3: Enable operation - Bit 4: reserved - Bit 5-6: Output cycle counter (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 7: Fault reset - Bit 8: Halt - Bit 9-15: reserved

Entry.Name: Position actual value invalid
Entry.Comment: This object shall indicate if the position encoder measured value is in invalid state.

Entry.Name: 1st Additional position actual value invalid
Entry.Comment: This object shall indicate if the first position encoder measured value is in invalid state.

Entry.Name: [SG] Statusword
Entry.Comment: This object shall provide the status of the PDS FSA. - Bit 0: Ready to switch on - Bit 1: Switched on - Bit 2: Operation enabled - Bit 3: Fault - Bit 4: Voltage enabled - Bit 5: Quick stop - Bit 6: Switch on disabled - Bit 7: Warning - Bit 8: reserved - Bit 9: Remote - Bit 10: Status toggle (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 11: Internal limit active - Bit 12: Drive follows the command value (cyclic modes of operation) - Bit 13: Input cycle counter (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 14: reserved - Bit 15: reserved

SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains parameters to manage the automatic motor brake control.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake type
SubItem.Comment: Activates drive internal automatic brake control.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake usage
SubItem.Comment: Configures the error reaction behavior of the motor brake.

SubItem.Name: Drive on delay time
SubItem.Comment: With the transition of the PDS state machine to "operation enabled" "drive on delay time" is started. The drive follows the command values after the "drive on delay time" has elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to unlock the motor brake before motion is enabled.

SubItem.Name: Drive off delay time
SubItem.Comment: After "operation enabled" of the PDS state machine is removed and the axis is in the standstill window, the locking of the brake is initiated and the drive off delay time is started. The torque/force remains activated in the drive until the configured drive off delay time is elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to lock the motor brake before the torque/force is switched off..

SubItem.Name: Motor brake current monitoring level
SubItem.Comment: If the motor brake current remains below the specified threshold, an error is reported. Motor brake current monitoring level is only active if brake control is enabled.

Object.Name: [SG] Controlword
Object.Comment: This object shall indicate the received command controlling the PDS FSA. - Bit 0: Switch on - Bit 1: Enable voltage - Bit 2: Quick stop - Bit 3: Enable operation - Bit 4: reserved - Bit 5-6: Output cycle counter (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 7: Fault reset - Bit 8: Halt - Bit 9-15: reserved

Object.Name: [SG] Statusword
Object.Comment: This object shall provide the status of the PDS FSA. - Bit 0: Ready to switch on - Bit 1: Switched on - Bit 2: Operation enabled - Bit 3: Fault - Bit 4: Voltage enabled - Bit 5: Quick stop - Bit 6: Switch on disabled - Bit 7: Warning - Bit 8: reserved - Bit 9: Remote - Bit 10: Status toggle (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 11: Internal limit active - Bit 12: Drive follows the command value (cyclic modes of operation) - Bit 13: Input cycle counter (see also Object 0x60D9 and 0x60DA) - Bit 14: reserved - Bit 15: reserved

Object.Name: [SG] Fault reaction option code
Object.Comment: This object shall indicate which action is performed when fault is detected in the PDS.

Object.Name: [SG] Gear ratio
Object.Comment: This object shall indicate the configured number of motor shaft revolutions and number of driving shaft revolutions.

Object.Name: [SG] Feed constant
Object.Comment: This object shall indicate the configured feed constant, this is the measurement distance per one revolution of the driving shaft of the gearbox.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: No Error
DiagMessage.Description: This Message is thrown always, if the Device enters an error-free state.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An Axis entered the error free state.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Short circuit (motor-side)
DiagMessage.Description: The drive hardware detected an over-current on the motor phases. The short circuit detection was triggered.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Continuous over current (device output side) Phase U
DiagMessage.Description: The drive software detected an overcurrent on the motor phases U.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Continuous over current (device output side) Phase V

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Phase U current offset out of range
DiagMessage.Description: The measured current offset of Phase U is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The device might be influenced by an external magnetic field.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the environment of this device for magnetic components.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Phase failure motor
DiagMessage.Description: The drive software detected an phase failure at the motor side. Please check wiring.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire is not connected properly to the hybrid motor connector.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power connections to the hybrid motor connector.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire in the motor cable is broken.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power wires in the motor cable.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The hybrid motor connector seems not to be plugged in properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check if the hybrid motor connector is plugged in properly.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: DC link under-voltage
DiagMessage.Description: An under-voltage occurred in the DC link circuit.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The DC link voltage level was under the configured minimum.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the minimum DC link voltage parameter. (Object 0x2C02/1)

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: DC link is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Axis got an enable command before DC link was ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Drive overtemperature shut down
DiagMessage.Description: The drive temperature has reached a critical value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The ambient temperature is too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Cool down the ambient temperature

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake power and power loss of axis are too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Lower the brake power and power loss of axis

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fan is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the fan

CauseRemedy.Cause: The cooling slots or the measuring sensors are polluted
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Clean the cooling slots and the measuring sensors

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Output stage STO active.
DiagMessage.Description: The Axis is unable to operate, because the Amplifier is locked from the safety module. (Safe Torque Off / STO)

CauseRemedy.Cause: The amplifier is locked by the safety module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the status of the safety module.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Supply DC link circuit is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply device is not ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check the Messages and the Status of the Supply Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply status is not alive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply controlword of this Axis Device is linked to the Power Supply Device and the Device is in EtherCAT OP.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply SDO communications are not finished.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply communication parameters and status of DeviceMain.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Factor Group Parameters: Feed constant illegal feed
DiagMessage.Description: The actual combination of the factor group Parameters is not allowed for this Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The feed constant - feed contains an illegal value (Object 0x6092/1 ChA or 0x6892/1 ChB).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please use a 2^{x} value (x from 16 to 28) for rotary encoders and a 10^{x} value (x from 0 to 9) for linear encoders.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: The range %u of the Position range limit is below the minimum accepted value of %u.
DiagMessage.Description: The range of the Position range limit (Object 0x6096 ChA or 0x6896 ChB) is below the minimum accepted value. The Range is calculated 'max limit' - 'min limit' + 1 and has to be positive.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The range of the Position range limit (Object 0x6096 ChA or 0x6896 ChB) is below the minimum accepted value. The Range is calculated 'max limit' - 'min limit' + 1 and has to be positive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the min and max value of the position range limit.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Position range limit Inc with remainder is not supported for primary feedback.
DiagMessage.Description: The position range limit is scaled internally to encoder increments. This calculation result contains a remainder, which is not supported for the primary feedback.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The position range limit is scaled internally to encoder increments. This calculation result contains a remainder, which is not supported for the primary feedback.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the position range limit and the factor group parameters of this feedback.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the position range limit and the factor group parameters of this feedback.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Object 0x%X/%X changed in EtherCAT SafeOP or OP.
DiagMessage.Description: This errormessage was created, because this change during Runtime is potentially dangerous, if you don't know what you do.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The value of the position range limit or a Factor group object was changed in EtherCAT SafeOP or OP.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Execute fault reset command.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Motor brake: Current monitoring error.
DiagMessage.Description: The motor brake current monitoring detected an insufficient current.
